properties.headline: High Wind Warning issued January 6 at 2:34AM MST until January 7 at 8:00AM MST by NWS Cheyenne WY
properties.description:
...STRONG WIND GUSTS TO 65 MPH LIKELY THIS MORNING AND
AFTERNOON. GUSTY WINDS WILL CONTINUE THROUGH TUESDAY MORNING...

The National Weather Service in Cheyenne has issued a High Wind
Warning, which is in effect until 8 AM MST Tuesday. The High Wind
Watch is no longer in effect.

* WHAT...West winds 30 to 40 mph with gusts up to 65 mph
possible.

* WHERE...East Platte County County.

* WHEN...From late tonight through Tuesday morning.

* IMPACTS...Damaging winds could blow down trees and power lines.
Secure loose outdoor items. Travel could be difficult,
especially for high profile vehicles.
properties.instruction:
Monitor the latest forecasts and warnings for updates on this
situation. Fasten loose objects or shelter objects in a safe
location prior to the onset of winds.

A High Wind Warning means a hazardous high wind event is expected
or occurring. Sustained wind speeds of at least 40 mph or gusts
of 58 mph or more can lead to property damage.

NWSheadline: HIGH WIND WARNING IN EFFECT UNTIL 8 AM MST TUESDAY
